parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the rear liftgate panel can cause the glass to shatter, leading to injuries or accidents. Additionally, it can also lead to water entry into the vehicle, causing further damage.
symptoms: Cracks on the rear liftgate panel
often near the Ford emblem
which can grow and spread over time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The peeling and rusting of paint can lead to water entry into the vehicle, causing further damage and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Peeling paint on the roof
hood
and trunk
often accompanied by rusting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rotting of the frame and weld issues can lead to the failure of the frame, causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Rotting of the frame
often along the welds
which can lead to the failure of the frame.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tire can lead to accidents or injuries, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Tire failure
often accompanied by damage to the vehicle's body.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or become unable to shift gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission warning light flashes
the vehicle shakes or jerks
the gears slip or hesitate
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission fluid leaks
or the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the reverse gear can cause the vehicle to jerk or lurch backwards, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or lurches backwards when shifting into reverse
the gears hesitate or slip
or the vehicle is unable to shift into reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle position sensor can cause the engine to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The engine stalls or loses power
the throttle position sensor warning light flashes
or the vehicle is unable to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the gear shifter can cause the vehicle to become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The gear shifter breaks or becomes stuck
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
or the gear shifter feels loose or sloppy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle's electronic system fails
the warning lights flash
or the vehicle is unable to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning fuel gauge can cause the driver to be unaware of the actual fuel level, leading to unexpected fuel depletion, engine stalling, and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The fuel gauge reads empty or incorrectly
the "Service Engine Soon" light stays on
and the fuel level sending unit may need to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty fuel pump or fuel tank can cause fuel leaks, engine stalling, and difficulty refueling, leading to potential safety risks.
symptoms: Fuel spills out of the fuel filler neck
the fuel pump may need to be replaced
and difficulty refueling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the "Check Fuel Cap" light can indicate a faulty fuel cap or a more serious issue with the evaporative emission control system, leading to potential safety risks.
symptoms: The "Check Fuel Cap" light stays on
and the evaporative emission control system may need to be repaired.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls without warning
and the vehicle may need to be repaired.
